{
  "texts": [
    "Both methods allow the determination of the full second-order elastic tensor, and through tensorial analysis the calculation of the various directional moduli and their polycrystalline averages.",
    "Due to the availability of the calculation of elastic tensors in quantum chemistry packages and the increase in high performance computing (HPC) resources available to researchers, several research groups started to perform systematic calculations on structural databases.",
    "Our group published in 2013 the first computational database of mechanical properties of zeolites at the DFT level, which was of modest size with 121 pure silica frameworks.",
    "In 2015, de Jong et al.",
    "calculated and published elastic information for 1,181 inorganic compounds, 20 which they deposited into the Materials Project database."
  ]
}